{
  "texts": [
    "In contrast, for smaller cracks, more advanced networks tend to produce better results for predicting cracks.",
    "We attribute this to the fact that the wavefield changes caused by smaller cracks are very insignificant, making them difficult to capture by sensors and more susceptible to irregularities in particle shapes and distributions within the material and measurement noise.",
    "This consideration also prompts us to contemplate amplifying such wavelength variations in the data.",
    "The evaluation of training the models with the normalization method is shown in Table 2.",
    "It presents all metrics on the selected model trained using a reference wave field."
  ]
}